race.comment: YOLO (3) is going well for this. The fresh win at Seymour was strong and two runs since have been good in stronger races, working home in a handy BM64 last time at Pakenham. The extra trip here can suit now and he rates highly. GREATHAM BOY (1) resumes off a handy trial placing. He can mix his form but tackled some better races last time in and did win fresh at Bendigo in that campaign. Respecting at odds. BANCOORA (5) resumes. He has form over a bit further but is right up to winning this and will be flashing home late. IT'S A YES (6) has bolted in with a trail since two poor runs this time in. This is a fair bit easier than last time however and his best form last time in would go awfully close.
